docs.text: Hash Function A hash function is any function that can be used to map data of arbitrary size onto data of a fixed size. Hash Functions DJB2 C++ 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 unsigned long long djb2 ( char * str ) { unsigned long long hash = 5381 ; int c ; while (( c = * ( str ++ ))) { hash = ( hash << 5 ) + hash + c ; } return hash ; } JavaScript 1 2 3 4 function djb2 () { return hash ; }
